Titulo: A High Power Density Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin (La0.9Sr0.1)0.98(Ga0.8Mg0.2)O3-δ Electrolyte and Nano-Scale Anode

Titulo: A High Power Density Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin (La0.9Sr0.1)0.98(Ga0.8Mg0.2)O3-δ Electrolyte and Nano-Scale Anode

Sentencas: Although high power density LSGM-electrolyte SOFCs have been reported, it is still necessary to develop a fabrication process suitable for large-scale manufacturing and to minimize the amount of LSGM used.
Titulo: A High Power Density Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin (La0.9Sr0.1)0.98(Ga0.8Mg0.2)O3-δ Electrolyte and Nano-Scale Anode

Sentencas: Here we show that SOFCs made with a novel processing method and a Sr0.8La0.2TiO3- (SLT) oxide support can achieve high power density at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: A High Power Density Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin (La0.9Sr0.1)0.98(Ga0.8Mg0.2)O3-δ Electrolyte and Nano-Scale Anode

Sentencas: The SLT support is advantageous, especially compared to LSGM supports, because of its low materials cost, electronic conductivity, and good mechanical strength.
Titulo: A High Power Density Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin (La0.9Sr0.1)0.98(Ga0.8Mg0.2)O3-δ Electrolyte and Nano-Scale Anode

Sentencas: The novel process is to first co-fire the ceramic layers - porous SLT support, porous LSGM layer, and dense LSGM layer - followed by infiltration of nano-scale Ni into the porous layers.
Titulo: A High Power Density Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin (La0.9Sr0.1)0.98(Ga0.8Mg0.2)O3-δ Electrolyte and Nano-Scale Anode

Sentencas: Low polarization resistance of 0.188 cm(2) was achieved at 650 degrees C for a cell with an optimized anode functional layer (AFL) and an (La,Sr)(Fe,Co)O-3 cathode.
Titulo: A High Power Density Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin (La0.9Sr0.1)0.98(Ga0.8Mg0.2)O3-δ Electrolyte and Nano-Scale Anode

Sentencas: Maximum power density reached 1.12 W cm(-2) at 650 degrees C, limited primarily by cathode polarization and ohmic resistances, so there is considerable potential to further improve the power density.
Titulo: A High Power Density Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin (La0.9Sr0.1)0.98(Ga0.8Mg0.2)O3-δ Electrolyte and Nano-Scale Anode
